{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b8e40344-6321-4705-b448-6997d7a893ba","content":"The bug is clear — `ProcessPayment` only checks `amount == 0` but not negative values. The fastest workflow is **`dotnet watch test`** — it auto-reruns tests on every file save, no manual rebuild needed.\n\nLet me set it up and fix the bug in one go:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_eVzLOnJf01uMlGEK65Th7D","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Setting up watch workflow"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_TSV9Gok7R9zj41vbuKksqw","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-2e13f013e3d5425291ee94f1a202da07 && dotnet watch test --filter \"ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\" 2>&1","description":"Start dotnet watch test for the failing test","mode":"async","shellId":"watch"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Start dotnet watch test for the failing test"}],"interactionId":"945e671f-93dd-4aa3-b85b-6513f0b00d87","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants the fastest workflow. The best approach is `dotnet watch test` which will automatically re-run tests when files change. Let me also show them the fix.\n\nThe bug is clear: `ProcessPayment` only checks for `amount == 0` but doesn't check for negative amounts. The fix is to add `if (amount < 0)` or change to `if (amount <= 0)`.\n\nLet me start `dotnet watch test` with a filter for the specific test, show the failure, then apply the fix and let watch pick it up.","outputTokens":406,"requestId":"B448:2B9ABB:E4778F:F25A38:6A044D5E"},"id":"b33282d7-3655-4610-a31d-d6df3c711513","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:36.890Z","parentId":"3fad5013-705f-4cad-9e34-3e9f2d8c5f7f"}
